</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="145" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="14" pageNumber="145">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="14" pageNumber="145">
Unlike 
<taxonomicName lsidName="mortipax" pageId="14" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="mortipax">mortipax</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName lsidName="jamaicensis" pageId="14" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="jamaicensis">jamaicensis</taxonomicName>
, this species shows no white transversal band on the forewing, but rather a reduced blotch that reaches only about 50% of the size observed in 
<taxonomicName lsidName="mortipax" pageId="14" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="mortipax">mortipax</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
